# Demandred · the general consumed by the Dragon's shadow

**Demandred** was Barid Bel Medar, a brilliant statesman and general in the Age of Legends — second only to Lews Therin Telamon in nearly everything, and consumed by his jealousy of the man who always stood one step above him. He turned to the Shadow the very day before he would have been honored at last, and became one of the Forsaken.

In the final turning of the saga he conquers and rules the eastern land of Shara in secret, then arrives at Tarmon Gai'don as the Shadow's mightiest field commander and one of its strongest channelers. He cuts down hero after hero in single combat, screaming for Lews Therin to answer him — until al'Lan Mandragoran, taking a wound to make the opening, finds the gap in his guard.

His nature is **natural** — for all his Power, Demandred is an embodied warlord and statesman, a man of armies and thrones and the oldest, most human poison: the refusal to be second. He is the Light's champion turned inside out.

